TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 This directory contains the CWL and supporting files needed to execute the designated Sounder SIPS L1a, L1b workflows.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The workflows execute the most recent version of the real (conteinerized) L1A and L1B PGEs.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Pre-requisites
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Read/Write permissions to an S3 bucket pre-populated with the required input files. For example, Read/Write permissions to the S3 bucket "s3://unity-sps-dev/" and "s3://unity-ads" in the AWS "jpl-mipl" account, where the Sounder SIPS input files have been staged.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Pre-download of the Sounder SIPS static data to a local directory:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <any directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-ads/sounder_sips/static_files/ ./SOUNDER_SIPS --profile <the AWS profile with the appropriate privileges>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - A python virtual environment with the latest version of the CWL libraries installed. For example, such an environment can be created as follows:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <any working directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 virtualenv cwl_venv
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 source cwl_venv/bin/activate
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 pip install cwltool cwl-runner
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - The latest version of the Sounder SIPS Docker containers built on or downloaded to the local laptop, which at this time is:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1a_pge:r0.1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1b_pge:r0.1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Steps
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Clone this repository and enter this directory:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 git clone https://github.com/unity-sds/unity-sps-workflows.git
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd unity-sps-workflows/
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 git checkout devel
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd sounder_sips
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Renew the AWS credentials for which you have Read/Write permissions to the desired S3 bucket. For example:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws-login -pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ...
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Please choose the role you would like to assume:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 [0] jpl-mipl / power_user ---->....
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ...
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Credential file /Users/...../.aws/config has been successfully updated. To use you must specify the profile 'saml-pub'.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Latest Sounder SIPS L1A, L1B Workflows
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The steps to execute the L1A and L1B workflows are practically the same.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Edit the file ssips_L1a_workflow_job_new.yml or ssips_L1b_workflow_job_new.yml which contains the specific user parameters used by the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - Adjust the value of _static_dir_ to the local directory where the Sounder SIPS static files were downloaded
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - cut-and-paste the value of the AWS keys (_aws_access_key_id_, _aws_secret_access_key_, _aws_session_token_) from the values for the selected profile included in the AWS credential file _~/.aws/credentials_ .
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Execute the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwl-runner --no-match-user --no-read-only ssips_L1a_workflow.cwl ssips_L1a_workflow.yml
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 or:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwl-runner --no-match-user --no-read-only ssips_L1b_workflow.cwl ssips_L1b_workflow.yml
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - After the workflow completes, verify that fake output files have been created in the target S3 bucket s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1a/out/ or s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1b/out, respectively.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Older Sounder SIPS L1a+L1b combined Workflow
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Edit the file _ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow_job.yml_ which contains the specific user parameters used by the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - Adjust the value of _l1a_workflow_source_s3_folder_ to match your S3 input bucket (where the input test file is stored)
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - Adjust the value of _l1a_workflow_target_s3_folder_ and _l1b_workflow_target_s3_folder_ to the desired S3 locations where the output files will be written (the target S3 folder must exist, but the target S3 folders within it don't have to)
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - cut-and-paste the value of the AWS keys (_workflow_aws_access_key_id_, _workflow_aws_secret_access_key_, _workflow_aws_session_token_) from the values for the selected profile included in the AWS credential file _~/.aws/credentials_ .
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Execute the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwl-runner --no-match-user --no-read-only ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow.cwl ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow_job.yml
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - {class: File, path: P1570515ATMSSCIENCEAAT16014215930700.PDS}

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                   path: /Users/cinquini/data/SOUNDER_SIPS
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:             EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:           + "sounder_sips_pges.md"       = <<-EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # Sounder SIPS PGEs
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 This page contains the instructions for executing the Sounder SIPS L1a and L1b PGEs as standalone Docker containers.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The two PGEs can be executed independently - i.e. the L1b PGE can be executed first without prior execution of the L1a PGE.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Below, `<some directory>` can be any directory, `<aws account number>` is the JPL MIPL AWS account number.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Renew the AWS credentials
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws-login -pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Credentials will be written for the _saml-pub_ profile.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Download the input data
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <some directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 mkdir input
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd input
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # for the L1a PGE:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1a/in/ . --recursive --profile saml-pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # for the L1b PGE:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1b/in/ . --recursive --profile saml-pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export PGE_IN_DIR=`pwd`
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Download the static data
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Static data is needed by both the L1a nd L1b PGEs.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <some directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 mkdir static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-ads/sounder_sips/static_files/ . --recursive --profile saml-pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export PGE_STATIC_DIR=`pwd`
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Set the Docker image and version
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Set the Docker image and version to use, for example:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # For L1a:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export DOCKER_IMAGE=<aws account number>.dkr.ecr.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1a_pge
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # For L1b
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export DOCKER_IMAGE=<aws account number>.dkr.ecr.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1b_pge
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export DOCKER_TAG=r0.1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Download the Docker image
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws ecr get-login-password --region us-west-1 --profile saml-pub | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <aws account number>.dkr.ecr.us-west-1.amazonaws.com
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker pull ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG}
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Execute the Docker container containing the PGE
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Mounting the local input and output directories to the default locations inside the container where the PGE will look for (i.e., '/pge/in' and '/pge/out'):
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker run --rm \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_IN_DIR}:/pge/in \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_OUT_DIR}:/pge/out \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_STATIC_DIR}:/tmp/static \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG} \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     /tmp/processed_notebook.ipynb \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -p data_static_path /tmp/static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Alternatively, mounting the local input and output directories to other locations inside the container and passing them as additional paremeters to the PGE
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 (note that the output directory must be writable by the user executing the PGE inside the container):
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker run --rm \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_IN_DIR}:/pge/inx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_OUT_DIR}:/tmp/outx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_STATIC_DIR}:/tmp/staticx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -w /tmp \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG} \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     /tmp/processed_notebook.ipynb \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -p input_path /pge/inx -p output_path /tmp/outx -p data_static_path /tmp/staticx
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Finally, also overriding the entrypoint:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker run --rm \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_IN_DIR}:/pge/inx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_OUT_DIR}:/tmp/out \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_STATIC_DIR}:/tmp/static \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -w /tmp \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     --entrypoint papermill \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:$DOCKER_TAG \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     /pge/interface/run_l1b_pge.ipynb /tmp/processed_notebook.ipynb \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -p input_path /pge/inx -p output_path /tmp/out -p data_static_path /tmp/static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The execution of the L1a Docker container will last approximately two hours and write output in the $PGE_OUT_DIR directory.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The execution of the L1b Docker container will last only a few minutes and again write output in the $PGE_OUT_DIR directory.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:             EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:           + "ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow.cwl" = <<-EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 #!/usr/bin/env cwl-runner
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwlVersion: v1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 class: Workflow
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 label: Workflow that executes the combined Sounder SIPS L1a +L1b end-to-end processing
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:                 doc: Requires valid AWS credentials as input arguments
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:51:20-07:00 logger.go:66:

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 This directory contains the CWL and supporting files needed to execute the designated Sounder SIPS L1a, L1b workflows.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The workflows execute the most recent version of the real (conteinerized) L1A and L1B PGEs.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Pre-requisites
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Read/Write permissions to an S3 bucket pre-populated with the required input files. For example, Read/Write permissions to the S3 bucket "s3://unity-sps-dev/" and "s3://unity-ads" in the AWS "jpl-mipl" account, where the Sounder SIPS input files have been staged.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Pre-download of the Sounder SIPS static data to a local directory:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <any directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-ads/sounder_sips/static_files/ ./SOUNDER_SIPS --profile <the AWS profile with the appropriate privileges>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - A python virtual environment with the latest version of the CWL libraries installed. For example, such an environment can be created as follows:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <any working directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 virtualenv cwl_venv
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 source cwl_venv/bin/activate
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 pip install cwltool cwl-runner
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - The latest version of the Sounder SIPS Docker containers built on or downloaded to the local laptop, which at this time is:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1a_pge:r0.1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1b_pge:r0.1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Steps
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Clone this repository and enter this directory:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 git clone https://github.com/unity-sds/unity-sps-workflows.git
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd unity-sps-workflows/
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 git checkout devel
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd sounder_sips
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Renew the AWS credentials for which you have Read/Write permissions to the desired S3 bucket. For example:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws-login -pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ...
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Please choose the role you would like to assume:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 [0] jpl-mipl / power_user ---->....
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ...
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Credential file /Users/...../.aws/config has been successfully updated. To use you must specify the profile 'saml-pub'.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Latest Sounder SIPS L1A, L1B Workflows
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The steps to execute the L1A and L1B workflows are practically the same.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Edit the file ssips_L1a_workflow_job_new.yml or ssips_L1b_workflow_job_new.yml which contains the specific user parameters used by the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - Adjust the value of _static_dir_ to the local directory where the Sounder SIPS static files were downloaded
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - cut-and-paste the value of the AWS keys (_aws_access_key_id_, _aws_secret_access_key_, _aws_session_token_) from the values for the selected profile included in the AWS credential file _~/.aws/credentials_ .
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Execute the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwl-runner --no-match-user --no-read-only ssips_L1a_workflow.cwl ssips_L1a_workflow.yml
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 or:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwl-runner --no-match-user --no-read-only ssips_L1b_workflow.cwl ssips_L1b_workflow.yml
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - After the workflow completes, verify that fake output files have been created in the target S3 bucket s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1a/out/ or s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1b/out, respectively.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Older Sounder SIPS L1a+L1b combined Workflow

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Edit the file _ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow_job.yml_ which contains the specific user parameters used by the workflow:

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - Adjust the value of _l1a_workflow_source_s3_folder_ to match your S3 input bucket (where the input test file is stored)
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - Adjust the value of _l1a_workflow_target_s3_folder_ and _l1b_workflow_target_s3_folder_ to the desired S3 locations where the output files will be written (the target S3 folder must exist, but the target S3 folders within it don't have to)
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                   - cut-and-paste the value of the AWS keys (_workflow_aws_access_key_id_, _workflow_aws_secret_access_key_, _workflow_aws_session_token_) from the values for the selected profile included in the AWS credential file _~/.aws/credentials_ .
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 - Execute the workflow:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwl-runner --no-match-user --no-read-only ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow.cwl ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow_job.yml
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```

TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:           - "sounder_sips_pges.md"       = <<-EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # Sounder SIPS PGEs
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 This page contains the instructions for executing the Sounder SIPS L1a and L1b PGEs as standalone Docker containers.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The two PGEs can be executed independently - i.e. the L1b PGE can be executed first without prior execution of the L1a PGE.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Below, `<some directory>` can be any directory, `<aws account number>` is the JPL MIPL AWS account number.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Renew the AWS credentials
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws-login -pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Credentials will be written for the _saml-pub_ profile.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Download the input data
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <some directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 mkdir input
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd input
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # for the L1a PGE:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1a/in/ . --recursive --profile saml-pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # for the L1b PGE:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-sps-dev/sounder_sips/l1b/in/ . --recursive --profile saml-pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export PGE_IN_DIR=`pwd`
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Download the static data
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Static data is needed by both the L1a nd L1b PGEs.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd <some directory>
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 mkdir static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cd static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws s3 cp s3://unity-ads/sounder_sips/static_files/ . --recursive --profile saml-pub
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export PGE_STATIC_DIR=`pwd`
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Set the Docker image and version
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Set the Docker image and version to use, for example:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # For L1a:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export DOCKER_IMAGE=<aws account number>.dkr.ecr.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1a_pge
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 # For L1b
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export DOCKER_IMAGE=<aws account number>.dkr.ecr.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/unity-sds/sounder_sips_l1b_pge
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 export DOCKER_TAG=r0.1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Download the Docker image
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 aws ecr get-login-password --region us-west-1 --profile saml-pub | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <aws account number>.dkr.ecr.us-west-1.amazonaws.com
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker pull ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG}
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ## Execute the Docker container containing the PGE
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Mounting the local input and output directories to the default locations inside the container where the PGE will look for (i.e., '/pge/in' and '/pge/out'):
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker run --rm \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_IN_DIR}:/pge/in \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_OUT_DIR}:/pge/out \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_STATIC_DIR}:/tmp/static \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG} \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     /tmp/processed_notebook.ipynb \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -p data_static_path /tmp/static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Alternatively, mounting the local input and output directories to other locations inside the container and passing them as additional paremeters to the PGE
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 (note that the output directory must be writable by the user executing the PGE inside the container):
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker run --rm \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_IN_DIR}:/pge/inx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_OUT_DIR}:/tmp/outx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_STATIC_DIR}:/tmp/staticx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -w /tmp \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG} \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     /tmp/processed_notebook.ipynb \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -p input_path /pge/inx -p output_path /tmp/outx -p data_static_path /tmp/staticx
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 Finally, also overriding the entrypoint:
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 docker run --rm \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_IN_DIR}:/pge/inx \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_OUT_DIR}:/tmp/out \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -v ${PGE_STATIC_DIR}:/tmp/static \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -w /tmp \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     --entrypoint papermill \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:$DOCKER_TAG \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     /pge/interface/run_l1b_pge.ipynb /tmp/processed_notebook.ipynb \
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                     -p input_path /pge/inx -p output_path /tmp/out -p data_static_path /tmp/static
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 ```
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The execution of the L1a Docker container will last approximately two hours and write output in the $PGE_OUT_DIR directory.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 The execution of the L1b Docker container will last only a few minutes and again write output in the $PGE_OUT_DIR directory.
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:             EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:           - "ssips_L1a_L1b_workflow.cwl" = <<-EOT
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 #!/usr/bin/env cwl-runner
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 cwlVersion: v1.0
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 class: Workflow
TestTerraformUnity 2022-07-25T15:54:15-07:00 logger.go:66:                 label: Workflow that executes the combined Sounder SIPS L1a +L1b end-to-end processing
